current_subtask:
  summary: Refresh the core feed in place after a successful one-tap import, with no page reload.
  findings:
    - Reddit import now completes successfully.
    - Independent touch/quiescence proof is green with zero automatic loads.
    - OPEN MY FEED changes only the hash, so the previous test incorrectly waited for a full load event.
    - The core app reads IndexedDB during rebuildState(), but that function is private and currently runs only at boot.
  fix:
    - inject one idempotent sideways:importcomplete listener into generated manual-app/app.js from readable studio/manual/apply.py
    - listener awaits rebuildState() and renders the feed only if the feed route is active
    - update the phone proof to wait for #/feed and a nonzero corpus count, while asserting total page loads remain zero
  current_ci:
    - overlay validation: success on head b17bef9
    - kernel parity: success on head b17bef9
    - touch import completion/quiescence: success on head b17bef9
    - phone proof: failed only because it expected a load event after OPEN MY FEED
  done_when: OPEN MY FEED displays the imported Reddit record through an in-place core refresh, with no reload and no stale feed state.

